table.body:
If you think someone's used your intellectual property without permission (sometimes known as 'infringing your intellectual property rights'), you should either:

- stop them 
- make a commercial agreement so they can use it

###Request in writing that they stop

You can write to them yourself or you can get a solicitor or specialist intellectual property lawyer to do it for you.

You can use members of the:

- [Chartered Institute of Patent Attorneys](http://www.cipa.org.uk/ "CIPA website"){:rel="external"}
- [Institute of Trade Mark Attorneys](http://www.itma.org.uk/ "ITMA website"){:rel="external"}
- [Law Society of England and Wales](http://www.lawsociety.org.uk/choosingandusing/findasolicitor.law "The Law Society of England and Wales"){:rel="external"}
- [Law Society of Scotland](http://www.lawscot.org.uk/ "The Law Society of Scotland"){:rel="external"}
- [Law Society of Northern Ireland](http://www.lawsoc-ni.org/ "The Law Society of Northern Ireland"){:rel="external"}

###Try mediation or arbitration

If your letter doesn't work, mediation or arbitration should be your next step. You may 
be able to reach an agreement, or a licensing deal.

You can use the Intellectual Property Office's (IPO) [mediation service](http://www.ipo.gov.uk/d-mediation-ourservice.htm/ "Mediation on intellectual property infringement"){:rel="external"} wherever you are in the UK.

Or you can find accredited mediators in your country from:

- [Civil Mediation Council (England and Wales)](http://www.civilmediation.justice.gov.uk/ "Find a mediator in England and Wales"){:rel="external"}
- [Scottish Mediation Network](http://www.scottishmediation.org.uk/ "Scottish Mediation Network"){:rel="external"}
- [Northern Ireland Mediation](http://www.mediationnorthernireland.org/ "Northern Ireland Mediation"){:rel="external"}

^Mediation usually costs around £1,000 per day.^

##If you can't reach agreement

You can take [legal action.](/intellectual-property-an-overview/legal-action-about-intellectual-property "Legal action about intellectual property")

*[IPO]: Intellectual Property Office

The Intellectual Property Office (IPO) can legally resolve some intellectual property disputes if you can't [do it another way](/intellectual-property-an-overview/disputes-about-intellectual-property "Disputes about intellectual property"). It can make final decisions on disputes about:

- [patents](http://www.ipo.gov.uk/types/patent/p-dispute/p-hearing/p-interpartes/p-fileproceed.htm "IPO patent dispute hearings"){:rel="external"} 
- [design right or copyright licensing](http://www.ipo.gov.uk/pro-types/pro-design/d-law/d-law-designright.htm "Design right and copyright licensing disputes"){:rel="external"} 

##Taking court action

Going to court should be your last option - you should try to [get an agreement](/intellectual-property-an-overview/disputes-about-intellectual-property "Disputes about intellectual property") first.

%A court case about intellectual property can be extremely expensive, even if you win.%

In England and Wales, the maximums you can get for cases you win in the Patents Court are:

- £500,000 for damages
- £50,000 for legal costs

There are no limits in Scotland or Northern Ireland, or if any case in the UK goes to the High Court.

This means that even if you win your case, you could pay more in legal fees than you get back.

If you really need to take your case to court, you should use a specialist legal adviser, like members of the:

- [Chartered Institute of Patent Attorneys](http://www.cipa.org.uk/ "CIPA website"){:rel="external"}
- [Institute of Trade Mark Attorneys](http://www.itma.org.uk/ "ITMA website"){:rel="external"}
- [Law Society of England and Wales](http://www.lawsociety.org.uk/choosingandusing/findasolicitor.law "The Law Society of England and Wales"){:rel="external"}
- [Law Society of Scotland](http://www.lawscot.org.uk/ "The Law Society of Scotland"){:rel="external"}
- [Law Society of Northern Ireland](http://www.lawsoc-ni.org/ "The Law Society of Northern Ireland"){:rel="external"}

*[IPO]: Intellectual Property Office
